CRUD-API-NODEJS
A simple CRUD REST API built with Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL to manage a fruits database.
The API automatically creates the database and tables if they do not exist when running the dev script.


NOTES
- Make sure PostgreSQL is running before starting the server.
- Default port can be changed in the .env file. 
- If your PORT doesn't work index.js will use PORT '5006'.


Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- PostgreSQL
- pg
- dotenv
- nodemon


Project Setup
- Clone the repository
    git clone https://github.com/danielmiguel02/CRUD-API-NODEJS.git
    cd CRUD-API-NODEJS

- Install Dependencies
    npm i

- Environment Variables
    Create a .env file in the root of the project and add your PostgreSQL credentials:
    DB_USER=your_db_user
    DB_HOST=localhost
    DB_DATABASE=your_database_name
    DB_PORT=5432
    DB_PASSWORD=your_password

- Running the project
    npm run dev


API Endpoints

METHOD       ROUTES                     DESCRIPTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET            /fruits                  Gets all fruits
GET            /fruits/id/:id           Gets fruit by ID
GET            /fruits/name/:name       Gets all fruits by name
POST           /fruits                  Creates a fruit (name, color, weight)
PUT            /fruits/:id              Updates a fruit by ID 
DELETE         /fruits/:id              Deletes a fruit by ID


Database Schema

id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY
name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
color VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
weight FLOAT


POST Example

{
  "name": "Apple",
  "color": "Red",
  "weight": 150
}


